https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=4f84983a07c3ee3ce0b0ec86717f1ec8

```rust

fn main() {
    let mut v1: [Vec<i32>; 1] = [vec![1, 2, 3]];
    
    let go = || {
        if v1[0][1] == 2 {
            println!("ok");
        }
    };
    
    loop {
        if v1.len() >= 1 {
            return go();
        }
        for i in v1.iter_mut() {
            println!("{i:?}");
        }
    }
}
```

Error:

```log
Compiling playground v0.0.1 (/playground)
error[[E0502]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/error-index.html#E0502): cannot borrow `v1` as mutable because it is also borrowed as immutable
  --> src/main.rs:15:18
   |
5  |     let go = || {
   |              -- immutable borrow occurs here
6  |         if v1[0][1] == 2 {
   |            -- first borrow occurs due to use of `v1` in closure
...
13 |             return go();
   |                    -- immutable borrow later used here
14 |         }
15 |         for i in v1.iter_mut() {
   |                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ mutable borrow occurs here

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0502`.
error: could not compile `playground` due to previous error
```

I don't understand why there's a problem there, because it's returning on the closure call: `return go`

The error happens because it's inside `loop`. If I remove `loop` it works:

```rust

fn main() {
    let mut v1: [Vec<i32>; 1] = [vec![1, 2, 3]];
    
    let go = || {
        if v1[0][1] == 2 {
            println!("ok");
        }
    };
    
    //loop {
        if v1.len() >= 1 {
            return go();
        }
        for i in v1.iter_mut() {
            println!("{i:?}");
        }
    //}
}
```
